When using the option to determine what time you should go to sleep to wake up by a certain time, when you go to set the alarm, it sets it for the time to go to sleep, not the time to wake-up?  Am I supposed to set a loud, obnoxious alarm to remind me to go to sleep?  Seems a bit counter intuitive.

Here's the problem - If I need to get up at 9am it gives a bunch of options all 90 mins apart. If it's 1030pm, I missed my time for 9am by 16 mins(1014). So now the options are to wait 75 mins & go to bed at 1146pm, or get up at 744. It seems counterintuitive that waiting or getting up 75 mins earlier would help with sleep, but maybe I need to try trusting it. I'm not there yet...the 75 mins seems valuable. That being said, if you're planning for tomorrow instead of right now, it's a great lifestyle app.
